    description: "Maison Perumal occupies a lovingly restored 130-year-old Chettiar mansion in the heart of the Tamil Quarter, its shaded courtyard and thick lime-plastered walls offering welcome respite from Puducherry's tropical heat. Operated by CGH Earth, the restaurant celebrates the city's distinctive Franco-Tamil culinary heritage, drawing inspiration from the cooking traditions of the Renonçant community, the Franco-Indian Catholic families whose kitchens evolved at the crossroads of French and Tamil culture over more than two centuries.\n\nThe vazhapoo vadai (banana flower patties) is an understated masterpiece, showcasing an ingredient deeply rooted in Tamil home cooking through careful seasoning and impeccable texture. The karivepillai varutha meen, fish delicately fried with fragrant curry leaves, demonstrates the kitchen's restraint and respect for fresh seafood, while the kothamalli meen porichathu (coriander fish fry) layers aromatic herbs over perfectly cooked fish without overwhelming its natural flavour. The menu balances heritage recipes with refined presentation, allowing guests to experience Pondicherry's culinary identity in a setting that feels entirely authentic.\n\nCourtyard seating is highly recommended whenever available. Combined with the mansion's architectural beauty and the restaurant's commitment to preserving Franco-Tamil traditions, Maison Perumal offers one of the most rewarding heritage dining experiences in Puducherry.",
    mustOrder: ["Vazhapoo vadai", "Karivepillai varutha meen", "Kothamalli meen porichathu"],
